data.value: Katso idea
Täysin yhden ihmisen kokemus ilman ryhmäpainetta

Kertosäe:
En tahtonut tapella, tahdo erota,
en kuvitellut koskaan tän loppuvan,
en tahtonut sua rikkoo, tehdä meille näin mut vaik
kuinka rakastaakin toinen toistaan jälleen satuttaa


Säe 1:
Anteeks kulta että en oo vähään aikaan soittanut
ollaan oltuu kiireisii ja työstä oon vain toipunut
Mul on ikävä ja haluisin sut tänne,
makaamaan rannal kun yllä loistaa tähdet
Mietin että olisit lämmin mun sylissä
vannoin pysyy mukanas ylä  ja ala mäissä,
Silti aika kuluu pois mut vieden
suudelmat sun on enää muistois mielen
Niinku se kosketuksen mielikuva, kun
suutelen sua ja me yhes keinutaan
ku ilta tummuu, ja kuulen vain sut
kuu loistaa suhun ja hikeen kastut
Kai molemmat yritti liian vähän koska
tultiin tähän eikä tarpeeks nähä
Kohta vielä palaan taas, tule rakas vastaan
Ollaan vielä viisaampii et voidaan taas rakastaa


Säe 2:
Tuntu niinku tarvitsin  jonkun toisen
nimes unohtuu ja muihin nimiin sen sotken
Kun mä viimeks lähin ovet paukkuen
tuli vastaan nainen uutta toivoo huokuen
Mä torjuin iloiset tunteet  mut meidän
katseet kun kohtas katos murheet
Miten tunteen sammutan?  En tiiä, mutta
otteeseen mut se saa,  en kiellä
Mä pelkään sitä taas  et ihastun
tai et rakastun ja petyn enkä palaudu
En haluu rakastuu toiseen joka heti jättää
aika on arvokasta kahestaan viettää
Enkä haluu yksinään tunnevuoristorataan,
mut sen kyllä kestää kun on joku jolle jakaa
En sulle tunnusta, että oot mun ainoa,
jos sä tahot niin, huomaat olevas mun vaimona


Bridge:
Välil sanoin et mua kaduttaa, tahdoin riidat unohtaa,
mut ne säilyy ain sun sisällä, vaik mä en huomaiskaan
Mä näyttänyt en tarpeeksi, kuinka paljon välitin
Voin mä olla taas nyt mukava, mitä sillä korjaisin

Chorus:
I didn't want to fight, I don't want to break up,
i never imagined this would end
I didn't mean to break you, to do this to us, but...
no matter how one loves the other, one hurts the other again


Verse 1a:
Sorry honey I haven't called in a while
I've been busy and I've just recovered from work
I miss you and I want you here
to lie down on the beach when there are only stars above

Verse 1b:
I dream how you would be warm in my arms
I promised to stay with you through the ups and downs
Still, time passes by taking me away
your kisses are memories in my mind now

Verse 1c:
Like that vision of us touching
in wich I kiss you and we rock together
when the night gets dark, and the only thing I hear is you
the moon shines on you and you are drenched in sweat

Verse 1d:
I guess neither of us tried enough
because we came here and don't see enough of each other
I'll be back in a moment, come meet me wife
Let's be a little wiser so that we can love again


Verse 2a:
I feel like I need someone else
I forget your name and I mess it up with another name
When I left with slamming doors last time,
a woman came up with an air of hope

Verse 2b:
I rejected the happy feelings,
but when our eyes met, the sorrows disappeared
How to turn off the feeling? I don't know
but sometimes it gets me, I won't deny

Verse 2c:
I'm afraid that I'll fall in love again
or that I fall in love, and fail and never recover
I don't want to fall in love with someone who immediately leaves
time is precious to spend alone with someone

Verse 2d:
And I don't want to ride the emotional roller coaster alone anymore,
but you can handle it when you share everything
I won't confess to you that you are my only one,
if you want, you will realize that you are my wife


Bridge:
Sometimes I said I was sorry, I wanted to forget the fights,
but they remain inside me, even if I don't notice it
I didn't show enough how much I cared
I can be nice to you again now, what would I fix with its
Katso idea
Maksimoi itsemääräämisoikeuden ja valinnanvapauden
Ihmiset vain toistavat huonoja piirteitään, eivätkä voi asialle mitään
'Satutamme toisiamme aina uudestaan' on melko rankaisevaa
Asenne on melko hyväksyvä kaikkia ihmisten huonoja piirteitä kohtaan
'katkeransuloisuutta, jossa henkilö saa helpotusta kielteisistä asioista' kuvastaa kertosäettä. Toisaalta säkeet on melko iloisia välillä.
Pohditaan vakavissaan omia tunnemyrskyjä ja mitä asialle voisi tehdä
Kevyet asiat sanotaan merkityksellisesti ja kohtalomaisesti, joten melko dramaattinen yleissävy.
Kertosäe on melko toivoton: 'satutamme toisiamme aina uudestaan'. Toisaalta, säe on melko toiveikas.
Asioista nähdään huonot puolet, etenkin kertsissä: 'mut ne säilyy ain sun sisällä'.
Avoin uusille parisuhteille ja seikkailuille
Uuden kumppanin tapaaminen on todella herkkää. Myös tappelu on herkkää normaaliin nähden.
Puhutaan vaimosta ja siitä että on vain yksi parisuhde kerrallaan.
Koko kappaleen eräs määrite on normaali heteroseksuaalinen parisuhde.
Kappalessa haetaan kauneutta normaaleilla parisuhdesymboleilla, jotka eivät ole kuitenkaan liian kliseisiä, kuten rakastelua hiekkarannalla.
Sallitaan miehen muuttuminen parisuhteessa ja ajautuminen omalle tielleen

Chorus 1:
I didn't want to have a quarrel,
I don't want to break up
I never meant to do this
never thought that this could end

Chorus 2:
I didn't mean to break us, do to us like this
We were loving each other, but hurting again

Verse 1a:
I haven't got time to call to you
I've een busy with work and healing from it
I'm missing you, wanting you near to me
to lying here on the beach with stars above

Verse 1b:
Dreaming of you, warm in my arms
Promised to stay through up and down
But time passed by,
kisses are memories

Verse 1c:
Memories of us touching
We kissed, we rocked together
When night got dark, I did hear only you
The moon was shining, you were drenched in sweat

Verse 1d:
Maybe both of us should have tried more,
but thank you for listening and apologizing
Let's be wiser again in our own worlds
maybe then we can find love again

Verse 2a:
I felt like I needed someone else
I was forgetting my ex-wife's name, and messing it up with another
I slammed the door when I left you
This new woman came with air of hope

Verse 2b:
First, I rejected the happy feelings
But when our eyes met, sorrows disappear
I didn't know how to turn off the feelings
I accepted them, won't deny

Verse 2c:
I'm scared of falling in love
And I'm scared of failing and not recovering
I am telling my love immediately
Time is precious when spending with someone

Verse 2d:
I don't want to ride on the emotional roller coaster alone
it's easier when you have someone to share it with
I don't confess that you're my only one
Maybe you will realize that you should be my wife

Bridge 1a:
I said I'm sorry and
I want to forget our fights
But our fights remain inside me
Even though you would not notice

Bridge 1b:
I haven't shown
how much I care
I can be nice again,
but what can I fix with it anymore

Chorus:
I didn't want to fight, don't want to part ways,
I never imagined it would turn out this way,
I didn't want to break you, do this to us,
No matter how much we love each other, we still hurt each other in the end.

Verse 1:
Sorry my love, I haven't been calling,
We both have had our share of busy days and trying to recover,
I miss you and I'd wish you were here,
Lying on the beach with stars as our ceiling,
I thought I could keep you warm in my embrace,
Promised to stay with you through the good and bad days,
Still time passed and all we have are the memories of our kisses,
Just the thought of us dancing together as the evening falls,
I can only hear you, with the moon light shining over you and me,
We both tried too little in our relationship,
Not seeing it coming, the chances of us being together are fading,
Soon I'll be coming back, come and meet me,
Let's be smarter and fall in love again.

Verse 2:
It felt like I need someone else,
Forgetting the name and filling it with someone else instead,
When I last left, the door swinging behind me,
I saw a woman full of new hope,
I rejected those happy feelings but when our eyes met, the worries faded away,
How do I turn those feelings off? I don't know but it still feels right,
I'm still scared of being taken away again,
If I fall in love and in the end I just break again,
I don't want to fall in love only to be left,
Time was precious when we were together,
I won't admit that you are my only one,
If you want it, soon you'll be my wife.

Bridge:
Sometimes I said that I regret it, wanting to forget the fight,
But they will remain buried in you, even if I don't notice it,
I didn't show enough love, what can I fix now?
Can I be nice again, what can I do with it?

1. What Steve Packard (born 2013, likes Pop-Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
-I don't want to fight and I don't want to break up. That's not how relationships should be. It seems like it's too late to repair the damage done, but if the damage caused by us still hurts one another, then things have to change for the better.

2. What Mila Smith (born 2009, likes KoreaPop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It's really sad to hear that one of them is always hurting the other in the end. Relationships don't have to end this way. There is always hope and something to work for. We just have to be positive and put in the effort.

3. What Paul Lee (born 2003, likes Rap) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- Sounds like someone is stuck in a cycle of pain and dissatisfaction. It's understandable that they want to try to make things work but it's important to make sure both sides are equally invested in the relationship. That way, both can benefit from it. 

4. What Tina Smith (born 1996, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- This is really heartbreaking. It's hard to maintain a relationship when one of you is always doing something to hurt the other. Relationships should be built on trust and understanding, not pain and disappointment.

5. What Bobby Reynolds (born 1995, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It sounds like the couple in the song have been through a lot and they are struggling to find the balance between being together and going their separate ways. It's hard to make a relationship work but if you both believe in it, it can definitely be done. 

6. What Rachel Johnson (born 1992, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- This is a tough situation to be in. It's hard to find the balance between staying in a relationship and leaving it. Both participants have to be willing to put in the effort for it to work. It's about having patience and understanding.

7. What Shawn Johnson (born 1991, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- You have to want to stay together. If it isn't worth the effort anymore, then it's time to move on. Relationships should be healthy and both partners should be willing to make it work. No one should be hurting each other in the process.

8. What Jake White (born 1989, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It saddens me to hear that even when they love each other, there always seems to be hurt in the end. Relationships should bring joy and happiness, not more heartache. People should strive to bring positive energy into a relationship.

9. What Cyrus McCall (born 1988, likes Rap) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It sounds like the couple in the song is stuck in an endless cycle of love and pain. It's hard to repair a relationship when one of you is always hurting the other. It's important to put in the effort to make the relationship work as best as you can. 

10. What Kelly Taylor (born 1987, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- This is a really difficult situation to be in. Love can be so complicated and can hurt so much. It's important to be honest with yourself and the other person in order to make a relationship work.

11. What Mike Richards (born 1977, likes Metal) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It's heartbreaking to see someone in such a delicate and painful situation. Relationships don't have to end up this way. It takes courage to hope for and stay in a relationship, and both parties have to be willing to work together and repair the hurts.

Things that seemed so fine,

I waved goodbye to our sweet den,

Now I know that I'm all alone,
Trouble is here, and not gone.

We might have been the perfect pair,
But that's not what I can bear,
Our love has been a long hard road,

I can't forget all of the times,

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
I've walked in circles,
not knowing where I'm going to be,
The silence never chirps,
nothing but misery.

My heart was filled with shame,
too afraid to stand proud and tall,
My spirit without blame,
what can make up for it all?

I gave it all my try,
but fear always pushed me down,
No one ever did cry,
I've given up on this town.

I've been so forlorn,
trying to find a way out of this maze,
But I'm still not newborn,
feeling ungrounded in this daze.

I never said goodbye,
instead I've been debating in my mind,
A question I should ask why,
something I'll never find.

I've always retracted,
showing fear of being hurt again,
Myself I've attacked,
there's no way to fix it then.

I was in the front row,
observing the world I was in,
Things got weird and slow,
I'm alone, where do I begin?

I've been searching for a word,
to express what I can't show,
My soul misunderstood,
where to go I don't know.

It's happened before,
being too scared to make a move,
My inner-self so sore,
but I was never able to prove.

I've never been me,
afraid of showing my true colors,
I'm stuck in between,
in a way there's no other.

I've kept my heart sealed,
not once was I to let it free,
Now all that I feel,
is it too late for me?

I have kept an eye,
waiting for my moment to shine,
No longer can I lie,
will I ever cross that line?

I'm tired of fakin',
wanting to break out of this prison,
My head keeps on shakin',
I'm desperate but with no mission.

I almost gave up,
too afraid to run my own race,
Fading beyond corruption,
with no one there to keep the pace.

I always felt so low,
afraid of the darts they'd throw,
My hope in a snowball,
what can I do to show?
